reviews.review_text:
Music Never Stopped made up for it I went to this show. I was really bummed with it. Then they played, "The Music Never Stopped." It blew my mind. It still does. I listen to it every single morning.

So, 7 stars for Music...

2 for the rest of the show.

Never Had Such A Good Time! This run was a mixed bag for me.  The first night (12/11) was, in a word, Underwhelming.  Super High Expectations (first Cal Dead Show since Garcia's ill-health earlier that year) - and the vibe I got that night was 'ugh.  here we go again.'  My buddy and I left that first show disheartened to say the least.   Fast forward a few days.  The 12/16 show Ripped.  We were back to being Stoked.   What would they do the last night?  Turns out - pretty much everything a guy could wish for.  The Boys were in a good mood onstage - when it came around to the last chorus on the opening 'Touch' Jerry shot Phil a look like "well, are we doing it tonight Man?" - and Phil responded with a tasteful but exuberant 'nudge' into the final 'we will get by'.  Loser is a highlight of the first set for sure.  At the end of Queen Jane Bobby was waving at/to the group of young female admirers at the front of the stage.  Music to close the first set let us know that they were 'locked in' for the night.

Look at the 2nd set on paper.  This was no 'going through the motions' set of music.  Pre-Drums Playin' Reprise - yes, please.  Post Drums HCSunshine was the first 'new' one in California - it was a delight to hear!  

In short - we left Oakland that night in great spirits, stoked for what the future might bring.  

To top it off this Matrix is about as good a sound as you can get!
